Simple picture: ‚Ä¢  Linear medium: Waves spread (dispersion dominates). ‚Ä¢  Nonlinear medium (Kerr effect): Intensity increases refractive index ‚Üí self-focusing. ‚Ä¢  Balance: Soliton propagates unchanged ‚Äî ‚Äúparticle-like‚Äù light packet. Experimental reality: ‚Ä¢  Temporal solitons in optical fibers (1980s‚Äìpresent): Pulses in telecom. ‚Ä¢  Spatial solitons in waveguides: Beams that don‚Äôt diffract. ‚Ä¢  Dissipative solitons in microresonators: Frequency combs (Nobel 2023 related).
